('Design', 'Product Designer', 'Portfolio', 'Craft & Visual Design:', '• Designs are outdated, inconsistent, or low-quality. • Layouts are cluttered, typography and color are weak, and interactive elements are non-functional or missing. • Portfolio is poorly organized or unprofessional.', '• Visual execution is inconsistent. • Layout and hierarchy feel uneven; prototypes or animations are rough. • Portfolio is functional but carelessly presented, with at least 3 projects from the last 6 years and coverage of both desktop and mobile designs.', '• Portfolio is professional. • Visual craft is strong, with polished animations, prototypes, and videos demonstrating good taste. • Includes multiple projects, both professional and personal, reflecting a variety of design experience.', '• Portfolio portrays a highly proactive and versatile designer. • Beyond excellent visual craft, the work demonstrates a curiosity to learn and experiment—incorporating motion, new tools, or varied styles. • Projects show a "builder mindset," where the designer pushes beyond the basic brief to elevate the final product feel through high-fidelity prototyping and creative exploration.'),
('Design', 'Product Designer', 'Portfolio', 'Product Sense & Strategy:', '• Shows little or no understanding of business context. • Problem is unclear. • Design decisions are disconnected from business goals. • Impact is vague or unsupported.', '• Shows some awareness of business context, but connections to outcomes are weak or inconsistent. • Projects tackle a small surface with limited revenue or impact. • Problem and business goals are partially defined, and impact is mentioned but not validated.', '• Clear understanding of the problem and business context for the assigned scope. • Design decisions are visibly connected to the stated goals. • The portfolio includes basic success metrics (quantitative or qualitative) or user feedback to validate the work.', '• Demonstrates strong product thinking. • The designer connects their specific feature work to broader business objectives or metrics (e.g., retention, conversion). • Shows initiative by referencing competitor analysis or data to justify decisions, proving they look beyond the immediate ticket.'),
('Design', 'Product Designer', 'Portfolio', 'Communication', '• Builds the foundation. • Communication is unclear or incomplete. • Explanations are missing or vague. • Design decisions are not justified. • Writing is poor, and hard to navigate.', '• Communication shows some structure but lacks depth or consistency. • Explanations are partial or overly wordy, suggesting excessive reliance on AI-generated text.', '• Communication is structured and logical. • Case studies follow a clear narrative arc (e.g., Problem → Solution →Result) without unnecessary fluff. • Explanations of why decisions were made are present. • May include a walkthrough video or clear visual summaries to aid understanding.', '• Communication is engaging and dynamic. • The designer moves beyond static text, proactively using formats like short video walkthroughs, GIFs, or interactive demos to simulate the final experience. • The narrative clearly articulates the "why" behind decisions, demonstrating a deep ownership of the project from start to finish.'),
('Design', 'Product Designer', 'Portfolio', 'User-centered problem solving', '• Little to no evidence of user-centered thinking. • Problem is unclear. • Process steps and validation are missing. • Edge cases are ignored. • Artifacts such as screenshots of post-its or FigJam boards are unreadable or pixelated.', '• Basic awareness of UX process. • Problem and user context are partially defined. • Research is synthesized to highlight main issues, with some validation of the problem. • Process steps are described superficially.', '• Demonstrates structured user-centered problem-solving. • Problem is clearly defined. • The problem is clearly defined, and solutions are grounded in user research or testing. • The process shows a logical progression (exploration,selection,validation). • Design artifacts are clean, readable, and relevant to the story.', '• Detailed execution. • Research is synthesized into actionable insights rather than just listed. • The solution considers technical constraints, edge cases, and error states, not just the "happy path." • Shows a willingness to iterate based on feedback and challenges assumptions proactively.'),
